Defendant Andrew J Katzka in court with attorney Joseph Smith.  Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to count 2 and counts 1 and 3 are dismissed and read-in. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS HUBER consecutive, w/Standard Release Conditions  

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No violent contact with any victim
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DOMESTIC ABUSE SURCHARGE $100.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 30 days huber, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  
6 days credit towards the condition time
Expungment is Denied.
